          "text": "Mixo has better design quality (8.0/10 vs 7.5/10). Mixo's templates are cleaner, more modern, with better typography and spacing. Durable's designs are functional but basic - they work but aren't memorable. If aesthetics matter and you want something that looks professionally designed, Mixo wins. If you just need a working site quickly and don't care about design nuances, Durable suffices. The design gap isn't huge, but Mixo has the edge for visual polish."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Does Durable's built-in CRM justify the extra cost?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "If you need CRM features, absolutely. Durable's built-in CRM saves $50-100/month compared to buying separate tools like HubSpot or Pipedrive. You get lead capture, pipeline tracking, follow-up automation, invoice generation - all included. For consultants, service businesses, agencies, this pays for itself many times over. If you're building a simple portfolio or blog, the CRM features are wasted and you're better off saving $3/month with Mixo. The CRM is only valuable if you'll actually use it."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which is faster: Mixo or Durable?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Both are incredibly fast. Durable generates sites in 30 seconds - the fastest we've tested. Mixo generates in 47 seconds - also blazing fast. In real-world testing, total time from prompt to published site was 15 minutes for Durable vs 13 minutes for Mixo. Durable's generation is 17 seconds faster, but Mixo's easier editing saved 2 minutes. For practical purposes, the speed difference is negligible. Both are so fast that setup time shouldn't be your deciding factor - choose based on features and price instead."
        }
